  "aims": "The aim of this module is to introduce the theoreatical foundations of database systems and the main concepts underlying practical organisation and management of such systems.",
  "objectives": [
    {
      "subheading": "",
      "items": {
        "DBS1": "appreciate the importance of database systems in information management",
        "DBS2": "be able to design and query a relational database",
        "DBS3": "have some experience with translating natural language queries into a logical formalism",
        "DBS4": "be able to create and manage an SQL database",
        "DBS5": "will have an understanding of some key concepts in database administration"
      }
    }
  ],
  "syllabus": "<p>This module covers the following topics:</p><ul><li>Introduction to database systems</li><li>Database Administration: basic concepts, database recovery</li><li>Entity-relationship modelling</li><li>A relational model of data</li><li>Functional dependencies and normal forms</li><li>Relations, model constraints, relational algebra</li><li>SQL</li></ul>",
